@startuml Use Case Diagram
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline
left to right direction

actor "User" as User
actor "Server" as Server

rectangle "Invisible-Chat System" {
    usecase "Join Room" as UC1
    usecase "Send Hidden Message" as UC2
    usecase "Receive Message" as UC3
    usecase "View Cover Feed" as UC4
    usecase "Access Hidden Chat" as UC5
    usecase "Configure Settings" as UC6
    usecase "Select Cover Image" as UC7
    usecase "Toggle Chat Mode" as UC8
}

User --> UC1
User --> UC2
User --> UC3
User --> UC4
User --> UC5
User --> UC6
User --> UC7
User --> UC8

UC1 --> Server : join_room
UC2 --> Server : send_message
UC3 <-- Server : receive_message
UC4 --> Server : (view public feed)
UC5 --> Server : (access via secret trigger)

note right of UC2
    Includes:
    - Encrypt message
    - Encode into image
    - Send via socket
end note

note right of UC3
    Includes:
    - Decode from image
    - Decrypt message
    - Display if valid
end note

note right of UC8
    Triple-click header
    to switch modes
end note
@enduml
